{
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionIn Society 5.0, proposed by the Japanese Cabinet Office, the goal is to provide necessary goods and services to those who need them, when they need them, and in the required quantities [1].",
    "This initiative aims to create a society where everyone can live comfortably and vibrantly.",
    "As digital devices evolve and user bases diversify, service usage scenarios have become increasingly varied, rapidly diversifying the services required by individual users [2].",
    "Even for smart home appliance services required by elderly individuals living alone, the conditions sought vary greatly from one user to another, depending on the extent of care services used, care needs, health status, specific preferences for home appliances, and the desired price range.",
    "The concept of service personalization entails recommending and providing services tailored to individual preferences [3,4]."
  ]
}